The paper deals with the formalization of algorithms for two different tree-based succinct representations, which are commonly used in data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the efficient representation of dynamic bit sequences, which falls under the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of Rank and Select operations suggests the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the implementation of these algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses the space-efficient representation of large amounts of data, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
